<div id="outline-container-humanities-anthropology" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="humanities-anthropology">Humanities &amp; Anthropology</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-humanities-anthropology">
<blockquote>
<p>
An inequilateral note about reading <i>philosophy</i>; the vast majority of philosophy books is
not worth reading, in fact it's painful to read it, which is a thing I realized too late (~1
year ago, thanks to a friend of mine allowed me to read his dissertation in <i>Obscurantism</i>
of philosophers), a lot of philosophy books I've read in my life was useful but not really
that 'useful', this is not the best place to explain why, but I'll talk about this in the
future Inshaa' Allah. Also, read <a href="https://sophy.ca/blog/2013/03/how-not-to-write-in-philosophy/">How not to write in philosophy &#x2013; Against obscurantism</a>.
</p>
</blockquote>
</div>

